mawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14356/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14356/canvas/1/5c3de5d4-bf7d-4e8c-8160-dfa73fa3d8d2","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-02T23:56:39.552Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds’s sketches punctuate the film. They are, on one level, ideal versions of what he hopes to bring to life through his art of dressmaking. The problem is that life is more rambunctious, like Alma. At the New Year’s Eve party, he’ll finally see her in her element—a contrast to a sketch that he can control with his hands.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14356/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:458.15684713375776,413.1016122611464,1200.6240047770698,358.8221536624204"}}}]}]}]}